<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="586" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,285]" box="[199,845,186,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,186,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Distribution</emphasis>
. Only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[608,656,187,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation box="[763,832,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1529,1553]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,186,1501]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[151,1436,181,1505]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution maps of Macrophyes and Mesilla species from Colombia, including the records of Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903 in Brescovit (1997)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506508/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,222,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Habitat.</emphasis>
The specimens were collected beating low shrubs, on foliage, in a conserved high mountain wet forest ecosystem, at 1313–1702 meters high.
</paragraph>
